<plot>Retraining for the Global Economy is a comedy that documents the devastating effects of globalization on the border city of Windsor, Ontario, and then dares to ask the question: Where do we go from here? Presented in the biz-speak of a mock training film, the answer is hilarious and heartwarming in this lighthearted look at our prospects for the 21st century.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?461420</url></doc>
